inner-container\">\n<h3 id=\"h-5-see-the-salt-marshes\">5. <strong>See the Salt Marshes<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Buy salt in France and chances are that it came from Ile de Re! The island is home to spectacular salt marshes and salt has been harvested here since the middle ages. Even better, they still farm salt using the traditional methods.&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--hotels \">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--hotels\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/go\/ile-de-re-accommodation\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">See all the accommodations on the island<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/02121330\/Ile-de-Re-france24.jpg\" alt=\"ile de re best things to do\"><\/noscript><img width=\"270\" height=\"338\" alt=\"ile de re best things to do\" class=\"wp-image-60869 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1536px) 100vw, 1536px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/02121330\/Ile-de-Re-france24.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/02121330\/Ile-de-Re-france24-480x600.jpg 480w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/02121330\/Ile-de-Re-france24-648x810.jpg 648w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/02121330\/Ile-de-Re-france24-270x338.jpg 270w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/02121330\/Ile-de-Re-france24-24x30.jpg 24w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/02121330\/Ile-de-Re-france24-130x163.jpg 130w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/02121330\/Ile-de-Re-france24-144x180.jpg 144w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/02121330\/Ile-de-Re-france24-614x768.jpg 614w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/02121330\/Ile-de-Re-france24-819x1024.jpg 819w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/02121330\/Ile-de-Re-france24-864x1080.jpg 864w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/02121330\/Ile-de-Re-france24-1152x1440.jpg 1152w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/02121330\/Ile-de-Re-france24-300x375.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/02121330\/Ile-de-Re-france24-600x750.jpg 600w\" tempsrc=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/02121330\/Ile-de-Re-france24-24x30.jpg\" src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png\" onerror=\"this.srcset='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.src='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.classList.remove('lazypreload'); \"><a class=\"pinit\" href=\"https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-pin=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/02121330\/Ile-de-Re-france24.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>We highly recommend visiting <a href=\"https:\/\/www.pick-sel.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">&#x2018;Pick Sel&#x2019;<\/a>, a marsh run by salt-maker Romain. He still uses artisanal methods to harvest the salt and is one of 100 Sauniers (saltmakers) left on the island. Back in the 19th century, there used to be over 1000! He&#x2019;s passionate about his craft and will teach you everything about salt production, the differences between coarse salt and Fleur de Sel, and how the salt marsh works in time with nature. Visiting the salt marshes is easily one of the top things to do in Ile de Re!<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--tip block-link--long\">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--tip\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><strong data-rich-text-format-boundary=\"true\">Tip:<\/strong> if you don&#x2019;t have time to visit the salt marsh itself, you can buy Romain&#x2019;s products at the market of &#x2018;Mail de la Couarde&#x2019; on Tuesday, Wednesday, Friday, Saturday, and Sunday.<\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/02121318\/Ile-de-Re-france23-1-540x810.jpg\" alt=\"ile de re france salt marshes\"><\/noscript><img width=\"225\" height=\"338\" alt=\"ile de re france salt marshes\" class=\"wp-image-60867 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/02121318\/Ile-de-Re-france23-1-540x810.jpg 540w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/02121318\/Ile-de-Re-france23-1-400x600.jpg 400w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/02121318\/Ile-de-Re-france23-1-225x338.jpg 225w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/02121318\/Ile-de-Re-france23-1-